ection using an example of a simple news feed application.","type":"text"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"project","references":{"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-04-Injection":{"title":"Dependency Injection","estimatedTime":"30min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to easily design dependencies and inject them into your scopes. Dependency injection simplifies the structure of your code by externalizing the management of dependencies, making your code more modular, testable, and flexible. In this tutorial, we will demonstrate dependency injection using an example of a simple news feed application."}],"kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-04-Injection","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-04-injection","role":"project"},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-05-Scopes":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-05-Scopes","estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-05-scopes","type":"topic","title":"Scopes","abstract":[{"text":"Defining all state and When events in a single Statostore doesn’t scale. We need to decide where exactly to split our state and events into separate state parts or Scopes. Sometimes separation is obvious and sometimes developers want to separate state and events that are inevitably coupled due to the nature of the business logic. However, this article will focus in how to separate the state of our apps in different scopes.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project"},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-04-Injection#Designing-a-Dependency":{"title":"Designing a Dependency","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to easily design dependencies and inject them into your scopes. Dependency injection simplifies the structure of your code by externalizing the management of dependencies, making your code more modular, testable, and flexible. In this tutorial, we will demonstrate dependency injection u